data.enText: an animal that lived millions of years ago but is now extinct (= it no longer exists) . There were many types of dinosaur , some of which were very large.

data.chText: 守旧落伍的人；过时落后的东西
data.enText: a person or thing that is old-fashioned and cannot change in the changing conditions of modern life

tr: any of numerous extinct terrestrial reptiles of the Mesozoic era

value.def: Dinosaurs were large reptiles which lived in prehistoric times.
If you refer to an organization as a dinosaur, you mean that it is large, inefficient, and out of date.
value.tran: 庞大臃肿的机构;过时的庞然大物
